{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9d6608d9-e6b5-4ee7-adc9-2e3dc933bc76","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform the runner-specific flags replace the old VSTest ones. You also need the corresponding extension NuGet packages in your test project:\n\n| NuGet package | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` | TRX output |\n| `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` | Code coverage |\n| `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` | Crash dumps |\n| `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` | Hang dumps |\n\nOn .NET 8 with `dotnet test`, platform-specific flags go after `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key flag mappings:**\n\n| VSTest (old) | Microsoft.Testing.Platform (new) |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n`--filter` stays the same and is handled before the `--` separator since `dotnet test` understands it natively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"931199bb-5a63-4def-8bb1-8bf3d07cecd7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a codebase task. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`  (same)\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx` \n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you use a different mechanism\n\n\n- `--blame-crash` maps to `--crashdump` and the hang-related flags become `--hangdump` with `--hangdump-timeout` for the timeout value.\n\nWhen running Microsoft.Testing.Platform projects through `dotnet test`, the CLI arguments get forwarded to the test runner, though the exact flag names differ from the VSTest runner. You can also invoke the test executable directly if you prefer, which gives you more direct control over the platform's options. -- `dotnet run` to invoke the test executable directly, or 2. Set an environment variable or project property to opt into the new testing platform behavior. On .NET 8, the default is still the VSTest bridge, so I need to be aware of that distinction when advising on the migration path.","outputTokens":1132,"requestId":"6806:24EAAB:297DA4B:2DCB928:69FD34A6"},"id":"b63de426-280c-411e-88be-0cb07424c31c","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:56:26.578Z","parentId":"6a7c73da-844a-4ac2-a77f-08b1f36946a9"}
